item.title: The 'last-mile' data problem is stalling enterprise agentic AI — 'golden pipelines' aim to fix it
item.description: Traditional ETL tools like dbt or Fivetran prepare data for reporting: structured analytics and dashboards with stable schemas. AI applications need something different: preparing messy, evolving operational data for model inference in real-time. Empromptu calls this distinction "inference integrity" versus "reporting integrity." Instead of treating data preparation as a separate discipline, golden pipelines integrate normalization directly into the AI application workflow, collapsing what typically requires 14 days of manual engineering into under an hour, the company says.
